#######################################
#  Solution

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_SOLUTION
The correct answer is ${BBOLD}A${EBOLD}.
Note that \( f'(0) = \displaystyle \lim_{x\to 0} \frac{f(x)-0}{x-0} \)
is \( 0 \) from the left (since \( f(x) = -x^2 \) for \( x < 0 \)) and 
is \( 0 \) from the right (since \( f(x) = x^2 \) for \( x > 0 \)).
Therefore, \( f'(0) = 0 \).
END_SOLUTION
